         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Copy ¶ Copy apparently made at Chief Secretary's Office. ¶ South Yarra ¶ Melbourne. ¶  ¶ 28/1/95 ¶ F. Reddin Esq ¶ Secretary to the Public Service Board. ¶  ¶ In compliance with the request of the Pub...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">95.01.28</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Francis Reddin</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">B95/3533, unit 581, VPRS 3992/P inward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>This letter is A95/1888 in the file.</p>
               </note>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Copy</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Copy apparently made at Chief Secretary's Office.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">South Yarra<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Melbourne.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>28/1/95</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">F. Reddin Esq</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Secretary to the Public Service Board.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In compliance with the request of the Public Service Board,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found; but see C. Topp to M, 7 March 1895<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>95-03-07a).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>dear Mr. Reddin, the two officers, Mr. Minchin and Mr. French,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Charles H. French.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>present themselves.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Without in any way endeavouring to influence the Commissioners in their independent judgment, I would beg to point out respectfully</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>1, that the officers are both trained through many years for the special herbarium work and that, as pointed out in former communications, there is ample occupation for them here;</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>2, that at the Herbarium at Kew (England)<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">eight</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>officers (all with considerable salaries) are regularly employed under the Director;</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>3, may I also venture to mention that on the present finance-year's Estimates Mr. Minchin and Mr. French are not mentioned as transferable, as they were in the year before;</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>4, that three years ago already enormous retrenchment was effected in my small Branch of the Public Service;</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>5, that the Melbourne Herbarium is the only one of vast magnitude in the southern hemisphere, commenced by me in 1839 and comprising nearly a million sheets.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I will gladly wait on the Commissioners if desired.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See also F. Reddin to M, 30 January 1895, and M to C. Topp, 8 March 1895<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 95-03-08a). Both Minchin and French were transferred by the Public Service Board to the Department of Agriculture (see E. Duffus to M, 5 February 1895), on the ground that they had been declared to be in excess in the Government Botanist's office.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>They returned to M on 3 May1895 (M to C. Topp, 3 May 1895).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
         </div>
      </body>
